cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI

This paper deals with optimization problems related to wireless networks, specifically in the context of localization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The use of robust optimization techniques and uncertainty modeling could also place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
